// ignore: constant_identifier_names
const Map<String, String> Lesson4ContentsMap_EN = {
  'L4T1': 'The Origin of Sin on Earth and Its Remedy',
  'L4M2':
      'For God so loved the world that He gave His only begotten Son, that whoever believes in Him should not perish but have everlasting life. - John 3:16',
  'L4P3':
      'We will study how sin entered the world, how Satan made this earth his headquarters, and what the remedy for sin is. The Word of God explains the origin of sin and provides assurance of victory and hope for the future. Our memory verse, which is perhaps the most beloved verse in the Bible, reveals that God has a personal interest and concern for humanity’s salvation. He gave His only begotten Son to save the world. No greater sacrifice could be made.',
  'L4S4': 'THE GARDEN: MAN’S HOME',
  'L4Q5': '1. Who created man on this earth? How?',
  'L4B6':
      'And the LORD GOD formed man from the DUST OF THE GROUND and breathed into his nostrils the BREATH OF LIFE, and man became a living soul. - Genesis 2:7',
  'L4Q7': '2. How was the first woman created?',
  'L4B8':
      'And the LORD God caused a deep sleep to fall upon the man, and he slept; and HE TOOK ONE OF HIS RIBS... and made it into a woman and brought her to the man. - Genesis 2:21, 22.',
  'L4Q9':
      '3. When God created Adam, what was man’s status in relation to all living creatures?',
  'L4B10':
      'Then God said, “Let Us make man in Our image, according to Our likeness, and LET THEM HAVE DOMINION over the fish of the sea, over the birds of the air, and over the cattle, over all the earth, and over every creeping thing that creeps on the earth.” So God created man in His own image; in the image of God He created him; male and female He created them. - Genesis 1:26, 27',
  'L4P11':
      'If you read Genesis 3:20, you will find that the first man was named Adam and the first woman was named Eve. They were made “in His image.” The animals, birds, and fish were placed under their stewardship to manage the earth.',
  'L4Q12': '4. What place did God give Adam and Eve as their home?',
  'L4B13':
      'And the LORD God planted A GARDEN in Eden, in the east, and there He put the man whom He had formed. And out of the ground, the LORD God made every tree grow that is pleasant to the sight and good for food. The tree of life was also in the midst of the garden, and the tree of the knowledge of good and evil. A river flowed from Eden to water the garden; and the LORD God took the man and put him in the garden of Eden to tend and keep it. - Genesis 2:8-10, 15.',
  'L4P14':
      'What a wonderful place for a home—a beautiful garden with magnificent trees and a clear, cool river. The animals, birds, fish, flowers, and trees were all perfect. There was no sickness, sorrow, or pain, and the animals were never wild.',
  'L4Q15': '5. What special warning did God give to the first couple?',
  'L4B16':
      'And the LORD God commanded the man, saying, “Of every tree of the garden you may freely eat; but of the TREE OF THE KNOWLEDGE OF GOOD AND EVIL you shall not eat, for in the day that you eat of it you shall surely die.” - Genesis 2:16, 17.',
  'L4P17':
      'God gave Adam and Eve everything good they needed or could enjoy. He allowed them to eat from the fruits of various trees. There was only one tree—the tree of the knowledge of good and evil—that they were to completely avoid, for its consequence was death. They were forbidden to eat from it. Disobedience would mean rejecting God—the source of life. Therefore, death would naturally follow.',
  'L4S18': 'MAN’S FIRST SIN',
  'L4Q19':
      '6. Read the sorrowful story of how the serpent deceived Eve and led both her and Adam to disobey God for the first time.',
  'L4B20':
      'The serpent... said to the woman, “Has God indeed said, ‘You shall not eat of every tree of the garden’?” And the woman said to the serpent, “We may eat the fruit of the trees of the garden, but of the fruit of the tree which is in the midst of the garden, God has said, ‘You shall not eat it, nor shall you touch it, lest you die.’” Then the serpent said to the woman, “You will not surely die. For God knows that in the day you eat of it, your eyes will be opened, and you will be like God, knowing good and evil.” So when the woman saw that the tree was good for food, that it was pleasant to the eyes, and a tree desirable to make one wise, she took of its fruit and ate. She also gave to her husband with her, and he ate. - Genesis 3:1-6.',
  'L4P21':
      'If you continue reading the following verses, you will learn that when God came down to talk with Adam and Eve, they hid among the trees in shame. They could no longer look at God face to face because of their guilty conscience. Similarly, when a child does something wrong that he knows is against the rules, he loses his confidence to look up.',
  'L4Q22': '7. Who is the serpent?',
  'L4B23':
      'So the great dragon was cast out, that serpent of old, called the Devil and SATAN, who deceives the whole world. - Revelation 12:9.',
  'L4P24':
      'The serpent that hid in the forbidden tree was none other than Satan, who was cast out from heaven. What a terrible deception! If only Adam and Eve had realized that it was Satan deceiving them. They disobeyed their Creator; they rejected God and sided with the enemy—Satan. They deserved death.',
  'L4P25':
      'How sorrowful the angels must have been when they carried the sad news back to heaven, “Adam and Eve have sinned.” What a terrible message to deliver in heaven.',
  'L4S26': 'THE PROMISE OF A SAVIOR',
  'L4Q27':
      '8. When the Lord came down to speak with Adam and Eve that evening, what message of hope did He bring?',
  'L4B28':
      'And I will put enmity between you (the serpent, Satan) and the woman (Eve), and between your seed (Satan’s followers) and her seed (a future descendant of Adam and Eve); HE SHALL CRUSH YOUR HEAD, and you (serpent, Satan) shall bruise His heel. - Genesis 3:15.',
  'L4P29':
      'This verse may seem difficult to understand, but the words within it help us see whom God is addressing. This is a promise that a future descendant of Adam and Eve would crush the head of Satan. Though it was mentioned that Satan would bruise the heel of the descendant—this was a prophecy foretelling Christ’s ultimate victory over Satan, which is certain, for He (Christ) will crush Satan’s head.',
  'L4S30': 'THE SAVIOR HAS COME',
  "L4Q31":
      "9. Before Christ was born, what news did the angel bring from heaven to earth?",
  "L4B32":
      "And she will give birth to a son, and you shall call his name JESUS, for HE WILL SAVE HIS PEOPLE from their sins. - Matthew 1:21.",
  "L4P33":
      "JESUS is the wonderful name that means 'SAVIOR.' The world waited nearly four thousand years for that Savior. Finally, the promised SON, the Child, came to save the world from sin. Jesus had a mother on earth (Mary) and a Father in heaven (God). No wonder He could bring heaven and earth together.",
  "L4Q34":
      "10. When Jesus was baptized, what clear evidence was given to the world that He is the Son of God?",
  "L4B35":
      "And when Jesus was baptized, He immediately came up from the water; and behold, the heavens were opened to Him, and He saw the Spirit of God descending like a dove and settling on Him, and behold, A VOICE FROM HEAVEN SAID, 'THIS IS MY BELOVED SON, in whom I am well pleased.' - Matthew 3:16, 17.",
  "L4P36":
      "Jesus was baptized before He began preaching, teaching, and healing the sick. At His baptism, the Father spoke these wonderful words, 'This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.' During His three and a half years of ministry, wherever He went, Jesus preached to the people and called them to turn away from their sins.",
  "L4S37": "THE DEATH OF JESUS AND VICTORY ON THE CROSS",
  "L4Q38":
      "11. How did the people treat Jesus when He reached the end of His ministry?",
  "L4B39":
      "The chief priests and the entire Sanhedrin sought false testimony against Jesus TO HAVE HIM PUT TO DEATH. In the morning, all the chief priests and the elders of the people conspired against Jesus to put Him to death... and they wove A CROWN OF THORNS and placed it on His head and put a reed in His right hand; and they knelt before Him and MOCKED HIM, saying, 'Hail, King of the Jews!' AND THEY SPAT ON HIM and took the reed and STRUCK HIM on the head... and they led Him out TO BE CRUCIFIED. And above His head, they placed the inscription written about Him: 'THIS IS JESUS, THE KING OF THE JEWS.' - Matthew 26:59, 27:1, 29, 31, 37.",
  "L4P40":
      "They crucified Him. This is the saddest scene in the history of the world. The religious leaders of that time hated Jesus because He exposed the sin in their lives. They were jealous because the people wanted to listen to Jesus. So they crucified Him. They did not realize that through His death on the cross, Jesus would save all who would come to Him for forgiveness and salvation. Jesus willingly died in place of mankind. All who believe in Him and follow Him will be saved.",
  "L4Q41": "12. What will Jesus do with our sins if we confess them?",
  "L4B42":
